        },
        {
          "type": "explanation",
          "name": "screen flash",
          "definition": "There are seven screen flash types:\n\nNONE: DST'= DST\nLIGHTEN: DST'= DST(1 - A) + C\nDARKEN: DST'= DST(1 - A) - C\nMAX: DST'= MAX[DST(1 - C), (C - A)(1-DST)]\nMIN: DST'= MIN[DST(1 - C), (C + A)(1-DST)]\nTINT: DST'= DST(1 - C) + (A*PIN[2C - 1, 0, 1] + A)(1-DST)\nINVERT: DST'= DST(1 - C) + A)\n\nIn the above equations C and A represent the color and alpha of the screen flash, DST represents the color in the framebuffer before the screen flash is applied, and DST' represents the color after the screen flash is applied."
        },
        {
          "type": "struct",
          "name": "screen flash*",
          "definition": "screen_flash_definition_struct"
